\@writefile{toc}{\contentsline {subsection}{\numberline {B}System parameters}{2}{section*.6}\protected@file@percent }
\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {II}{\ignorespaces Polariton analog horizon parameters for the LKB Paris platform. Both smooth (red / purple traces in Falque Fig.~2) and steep (Falque \S  IV.2) horizon configurations are reported by the primary source. The smooth-horizon value is used as the baseline throughout this paper; steep-horizon results are quoted as the platform's demonstrated upper reach. At steep horizon, $D = 0.93$ places the system in the non-perturbative regime where the leading $-\pi D^2/6$ correction is $\sim $46\%, so those predictions are leading-order only.}}{2}{table.2}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:params}{{II}{2}{Polariton analog horizon parameters for the LKB Paris platform. Both smooth (red / purple traces in Falque Fig.~2) and steep (Falque \S IV.2) horizon configurations are reported by the primary source. The smooth-horizon value is used as the baseline throughout this paper; steep-horizon results are quoted as the platform's demonstrated upper reach. At steep horizon, $D = 0.93$ places the system in the non-perturbative regime where the leading $-\pi D^2/6$ correction is $\sim $46\%, so those predictions are leading-order only}{table.2}{}}
